<p><b><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">Behavior</font></b></p>
<p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">TaskPad initially starts 
  up in the upper right side of your screen. From there, you may move or resize 
  it as you like. It will remmeber where you left if for the next time you use 
  it. Just move the mouse over any of the sides, top or bottom and the borders 
  will change to sizeable borders. When done, just click inside or off of TaskPad 
  and it will &quot;lock&quot; onto its position.</font></p>
<p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><b><font size="2">How to Use TaskPad:</font></b></font></p>
<p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><b><font size="2">Hot Keys</font></b></font></p>
<ol>
  <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">Ctrl + S (Saves Task 
    File)</font></li>
  <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">Ctrl + B (Set Bullet 
    List)</font></li>
  <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">Ctrl + Right (Increase 
    Indent)</font></li>
  <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">Ctrl + Left (Decrease 
    Indent)</font></li>
  <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">Ctrl + Tab (Tab)</font></li>
  <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">Usual hot key combos 
    for text apply; (Ctrl+ A, C, V, X, Y, Z) perform select all, copy, paste, 
    cut, redo and undo respectively.</font></li>
</ol>
